  <entry>
    <title>Wannier90 霍尔电导率的计算(AHC)</title>
    <link href="/year/04/27/Wannier90-%E9%9C%8D%E5%B0%94%E7%94%B5%E5%AF%BC%E7%8E%87%E7%9A%84%E8%AE%A1%E7%AE%97-AHC/"/>
    <url>/year/04/27/Wannier90-%E9%9C%8D%E5%B0%94%E7%94%B5%E5%AF%BC%E7%8E%87%E7%9A%84%E8%AE%A1%E7%AE%97-AHC/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="wannier90vasp霍尔电导率计算">Wannier90+vasp霍尔电导率计算</h1><blockquote><p>最近在算AHC，找了一篇比较好的<ahref="%5BPhys.%20Rev.%20B%20103,%20045114%20(2021)%20-%20Tunable%20anomalous%20Hall%20transport%20in%20bulk%20and%20two-dimensional%20$1T\ensuremath%7B-%7D%7B\mathrm%7BCrTe%7D%7D_%7B2%7D$:%20A%20first-principles%20study%20(aps.org)%5D(https://journals.aps.org/prb/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevB.103.045114)">PRB文章</a>来复刻下他们的计算过程</p></blockquote><h2 id="软件准备">软件准备</h2><ul><li><p>这篇文章是用wannier90包来构建紧束缚模型，然后使用wannier90自带的postw90.x来计算Berry曲率和反常霍尔电导率的计算。需要经过wannier90编译的vasp来构建Hamilton量，编译过程就不写了以后有机会单独写一篇这些计算软件的编译。</p></li><li><p>Ms上随便找了个POSCAR</p><figure class="highlight dos"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><div class="code-wrapper"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br></pre></div></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs dos"> <span class="hljs-built_in">Title</span><br>   <span class="hljs-number">1</span>.<span class="hljs-number">000</span><br>    <span class="hljs-number">3</span>.<span class="hljs-number">7074100970999999</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span><br>   -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>.<span class="hljs-number">8537050486000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">3</span>.<span class="hljs-number">2107113263999998</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span><br>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span>   <span class="hljs-number">21</span>.<span class="hljs-number">9708099365000002</span><br>   Cr   Te<br>    <span class="hljs-number">1</span>    <span class="hljs-number">2</span><br>Direct<br>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0000000000000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">5000000075000000</span>    Cr1<br>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">3333329860000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">6666669850000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">5754870105000001</span>    Te1<br>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">6666669850000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">3333329860000000</span>    <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">4245129895000000</span>    Te2<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>写入对应的INCAR</p><figure class="highlight apache"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs apache"><span class="hljs-attribute">Global</span> Parameters<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISTART</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">1</span>            (Read existing wavefunction; if there)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ICHARG</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>         (Non-self-consistent: GGA/LDA band structures)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ENCUT</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">520</span>       (Cut-<span class="hljs-literal">off</span> energy for plane wave basis set, in eV)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LCHARG</span> = .TRUE.        (Write CHGCAR or not)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">Electronic</span> Relaxation<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISMEAR</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>            (Gaussian smearing; metals:<span class="hljs-number">1</span>)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">SIGMA</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">05</span>         (Smearing value in eV; metals:<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">2</span>)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NELM</span>   =  <span class="hljs-number">90</span>           (Max electronic SCF steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NELMIN</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">6</span>            (Min electronic SCF steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">EDIFF</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">1</span>E-<span class="hljs-number">07</span>        (SCF energy convergence; in eV)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">Ionic</span> Relaxation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NSW</span>    =  <span class="hljs-number">100</span>          (Max ionic steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">IBRION</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>            (Algorithm: <span class="hljs-number">0</span>-MD; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>-Quasi-New; <span class="hljs-number">2</span>-CG)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISIF</span>   =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>            (Stress/relaxation: <span class="hljs-number">2</span>-Ions, <span class="hljs-number">3</span>-Shape/Ions/V, <span class="hljs-number">4</span>-Shape/Ions)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">EDIFFG</span> =  -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>E-<span class="hljs-number">02</span>        (Ionic convergence; eV/AA)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">Collinear</span> Magnetic Calculation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISPIN</span>      =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>        (Spin polarised DFT)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">MAGMOM</span>     = <span class="hljs-number">5</span> <span class="hljs-number">4</span> <span class="hljs-number">4</span>           (Set this parameters manually)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">DFT</span>+U Calculation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAU</span>   = .TRUE.        (Activate DFT+U)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDATYPE</span>=  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>            (Dudarev; only U-J matters)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUL</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>         (Orbitals for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUU</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>         (U for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUJ</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>         (J for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LMAXMIX</span>=  <span class="hljs-number">4</span>            (Mixing cut-<span class="hljs-literal">off</span>; <span class="hljs-number">4</span>-d, <span class="hljs-number">6</span>-f)<br><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>然后复制relaxation文件里的CONTCAR继续计算，略微修改INCAR文件如下：</p><figure class="highlight apache"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs apache"><span class="hljs-attribute">Global</span> Parameters<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISTART</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">1</span>            (Read existing wavefunction; if there)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ICHARG</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>         (Non-self-consistent: GGA/LDA band structures)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ENCUT</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">520</span>       (Cut-<span class="hljs-literal">off</span> energy for plane wave basis set, in eV)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LCHARG</span> = .TRUE.        (Write CHGCAR or not)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">Electronic</span> Relaxation<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISMEAR</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>            (Gaussian smearing; metals:<span class="hljs-number">1</span>)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">SIGMA</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">05</span>         (Smearing value in eV; metals:<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">2</span>)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NELM</span>   =  <span class="hljs-number">90</span>           (Max electronic SCF steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NELMIN</span> =  <span class="hljs-number">6</span>            (Min electronic SCF steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">EDIFF</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">1</span>E-<span class="hljs-number">07</span>        (SCF energy convergence; in eV)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">Ionic</span> Relaxation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">NSW</span>    =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>          (Max ionic steps)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">IBRION</span> =  -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>            (Algorithm: <span class="hljs-number">0</span>-MD; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>-Quasi-New; <span class="hljs-number">2</span>-CG)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISIF</span>   =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>            (Stress/relaxation: <span class="hljs-number">2</span>-Ions, <span class="hljs-number">3</span>-Shape/Ions/V, <span class="hljs-number">4</span>-Shape/Ions)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">EDIFFG</span> =  -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>E-<span class="hljs-number">02</span>        (Ionic convergence; eV/AA)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">Collinear</span> Magnetic Calculation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">ISPIN</span>      =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>        (Spin polarised DFT)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">MAGMOM</span>     = <span class="hljs-number">5</span> <span class="hljs-number">4</span> <span class="hljs-number">4</span>           (Set this parameters manually)<br><br><span class="hljs-attribute">DFT</span>+U Calculation<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAU</span>   = .TRUE.        (Activate DFT+U)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDATYPE</span>=  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>            (Dudarev; only U-J matters)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUL</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>         (Orbitals for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUU</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>         (U for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LDAUJ</span>  =  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>         (J for each species)<br><span class="hljs-attribute">LMAXMIX</span>=  <span class="hljs-number">4</span>            (Mixing cut-<span class="hljs-literal">off</span>; <span class="hljs-number">4</span>-d, <span class="hljs-number">6</span>-f)<br><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>然后就是第三步，最重要的一步，读取SCF文件夹产生的CHGCAR文件。加入SOC和WANNIER90开关。INCAR文件如下:</p><figure class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs">  <br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><div class="note note-success">            <p>注意</p>          </div><p>这里需要说明几个很重要的细节：</p><ul><li><p>第一点就是选取自旋轨道耦合轴方向参数SAXIS，这里需要注意的是三个方向选取的不同会造成不同的结果，因为<spanclass="math inline">\(CrTe_2\)</span>的对称性有Mx对称性，这就导致我们把磁向对准X轴方向的时候，会导致在全空间Berry曲率积分为0，也就是反常霍尔电导率消失。这里涉及到了磁群对称性的细节，有空写一篇分享。</p></li><li><p>第二点细节就是不同版本的Wannier90调用方式不同，我使用的是3.1版本，直接在INCAR中加入调用tag，并且直接写入win文件。低版本的wannier90可能需要手动创建win文件来供Vasp读取。</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="wannier90过程">WANNIER90过程</h2><h3 id="参数的构建">参数的构建</h3><ul><li>在第三步的win文件中我们需要写入一些提供给wannier90计算的参数，现在围绕材料来阐明一下参数是如何构建的，其实<ahref="%5BHigh-quality%20Wannier%20functions%20–%20WannierTools%5D(https://www.wanniertools.org/tutorials/high-quality-wfs/)">Wu老师</a>写过一篇很好的介绍，Wu老师开发了Wanniertools这款拓扑性质计算软件，有需要的朋友可以去尝试一下这款很成熟的软件。</li><li>对于构造一个材料的wannier函数过程只有三步：<ol type="1"><li>确定费米面附近能带的轨道构成</li><li>根据轨道构成确定你需要拟合几个wannier函数。</li><li>根据脚本来确定你能量窗口的选择。</li></ol></li></ul><h3 id="详细过程">详细过程</h3><ul><li>首先做一个DOS图，来观察一下费米面附近的能量的轨道分布情况，我这里做了DOS之后发现费米面附近的基本都是由Cr的d轨道的Te的p轨道构成(可以做更详细的轨道分布，例如:Pxdx-dy)。</li><li>确定了轨道之后，根据轨道来决定拟合的wannier波函数的数量，例如：我的DOS显示，在材料的费米能级附近只有Cr的d轨道和Te的p轨道贡献大(其余的跟它俩比实在是太小了，如果不放心可以看后面拟合的结果，如果拟合的结果很差再回来考虑其余这几个轨道)</li></ul>]]></content>
    
    
